Points for weapons.
============================
When putting in added affects a weapon recieves points.  To determine 
this you go by the level of the weapon.  i.e. A level 55 weapon 
recieves 110 points.  These points can be used according to the chart
below.  The formula for figuring out the points for a weapon would be
(weapon level) * 2 = Points. 


 Point chart:
============================
1 point      = 1 mana
1 point      = 1 hp
1 point      = 5 move
5 points     = 1 save, savingbreath, savingpara, savingrod, etc.
5 points     = 1 ac
5 points     = 1 stat (str,dex,con,wis, or int)
10 points    = 1 hitroll
10 points    = 1 damroll
10 points    = vorpal, and sharp, each
20 points    = vampiric, flaming, shocking, frost, and poison, each
-10 points   = two handed

You can also add negative effects.  For example a level 65 weapon with
-30 hps.  You take half of the -30 and add it for extra points, thus 
the weapon would have 80 points.  Another example is a level 40 weapon
with -2 damroll would recieve half of those points.  So it would be 50
points.

Please remember when creating weapons to make diverse weapons.  Not just
swords, daggers, and the like.  Try to keep a good mix of weapons in your area.

The only exception to these stats are powerweapons.  These stats are onlyto be created after
checking with an IMM 108+.
